From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dimitris Panokostas <midwan@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 20:12:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] accel/tcg: UAE synchronous PPC flush at cpu_exec safe point

Consume uae_flush_requested (set by the m68k thread when it patched PPC code /
page tables in shared RAM, #2114) on the PPC vcpu at the top of the cpu_exec
inner loop -- a safe point between TBs in serial context, the only place QEMU 11
allows a synchronous tb/tlb flush. Doing it here (instead of an async/queued
flush from the m68k thread, which lands too late) lets the PPC re-read the
patched code before it executes it, fixing the WarpOS handshake deadlock.
---
 accel/tcg/cpu-exec.c | 22 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 22 insertions(+)

--- a/accel/tcg/cpu-exec.c
+++ b/accel/tcg/cpu-exec.c
@@ -46,6 +46,19 @@
 #include "tb-context.h"
 #include "tb-internal.h"
 #include "internal-common.h"
+#include "exec/tb-flush.h"
+#include "exec/cputlb.h"
+
+/*
+ * UAE (BlitterStudio/amiberry#2114): set by the m68k thread (ppc_cpu_flush_jit
+ * in uae/qemu-uae-cpu.c) when it has patched PPC code or page tables directly in
+ * shared RAM, bypassing the PPC softmmu. It is consumed synchronously by the PPC
+ * vcpu in cpu_exec_loop() below -- a safe point between TBs in serial context,
+ * the only place QEMU 11 permits a synchronous TB flush. A flush from the m68k
+ * thread asserts (not a vcpu in serial context); an async/queued flush lands too
+ * late and the WarpOS m68k<->PPC handshake has already desynced.
+ */
+extern int uae_flush_requested;
 
 /* -icount align implementation. */
 
@@ -940,6 +953,18 @@
         int tb_exit = 0;
 
         while (!cpu_handle_interrupt(cpu, &last_tb)) {
+            /*
+             * UAE #2114: the m68k patched PPC code / page tables in shared RAM.
+             * We are at a safe point between TBs in serial context, so flush
+             * synchronously here -- before executing the next (possibly stale)
+             * TB. This is the one place in QEMU 11 a synchronous flush is legal.
+             */
+            if (qatomic_read(&uae_flush_requested)) {
+                qatomic_set(&uae_flush_requested, 0);
+                tlb_flush(cpu);
+                tb_flush__exclusive_or_serial();
+                last_tb = NULL;
+            }
             TranslationBlock *tb;
             TCGTBCPUState s = cpu->cc->tcg_ops->get_tb_cpu_state(cpu);
             s.cflags = cpu->cflags_next_tb;
